parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine and loss of power can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine shuts off without warning

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt and chain can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
The failure of the computer chip can cause the engine to shut off, leading to loss of control and potential accidents, as well as overheating and battery discharge.
The closure of the throttle body plate can cause the engine to shut off, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: the throttle body plate closes during self-cleaning mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Cruise Control Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine, especially when driving at high speeds, can increase the risk of accidents and leave the driver stranded. Additionally, the malfunction of the cruise control system can cause inconvenience and discomfort during long drives.
symptoms: The engine cuts off or stalls while driving
especially when turning off the highway
the cruise control system does not function

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause a loss of power steering and power brakes, making it difficult to control the vehicle, especially at high speeds, which can lead to accidents and put the lives of occupants at risk.
symptoms: the power steering and power brakes are inoperable
the vehicle must be coasted to a stop and put in "park" before it will restart.
